<!-- CSS -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/signup.css">
<link rel="web icon" type="png" href="images/webicon.png">
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/pikaday/css/pikaday.css">
<!-- Body -->
<nav class="navbar">
    <a href="/" class="logo">
        <span class="rental">Rental</span><span class="hub">Hub</span>
    </a>
</nav>

<div class="container">
    <h2>Create an Account</h2>
    <form id="signup-form" onsubmit="signup(event)">
        <input type="text" id="first-name" placeholder="First Name">
        <p id="first-name-error" class="error-message"></p>

        <input type="text" id="last-name" placeholder="Last Name">
        <p id="last-name-error" class="error-message"></p>

        <input type="text" id="birth-date" placeholder="Birthdate">
        <p id="birth-date-error" class="error-message"></p>

        <input type="text" id="contact-number" placeholder="Contact Number">
        <p id="contact-error" class="error-message"></p>

        <input type="email" id="email" placeholder="Email">
        <p id="email-error" class="error-message"></p>

        <div class="input-group">
            <div style="position: relative; width: 48%;">
                <input type="password" id="signup-password" placeholder="Password" 
                       oninput="handlePasswordInput('signup-password')" 
                       oncopy="return false" onpaste="return false" oncut="return false">
                <span class="toggle-password" onclick="togglePassword('signup-password')" id="toggle-signup-password"></span>
            </div>
            <div style="position: relative;;">
                <input type="password" id="confirm-password" placeholder="Re-enter Password"
                       oninput="handlePasswordInput('confirm-password')" 
                       oncopy="return false" onpaste="return false" oncut="return false">
                <span class="toggle-password" onclick="togglePassword('confirm-password')" id="toggle-confirm-password"></span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p id="password-error" class="error-message"></p>
        

        <!-- Terms and Conditions Checkbox -->
        <div class="terms-container">
            <input type="checkbox" id="terms-checkbox" required class="terms-checkbox">
            <label for="terms-checkbox" class="terms-label">I agree to the
                <span id="open-terms" class="terms-link">Terms and Conditions</span>
            </label>
        </div>

        <!-- Terms and Conditions Modal -->
        <div id="modal-overlay" class="modal-overlay"></div>
        <div id="terms-modal" class="modal">
            <div class="modal-content">
                <span class="close-btn">&times;</span>
                <p class="termsandcondi">
                <h3>Terms and Conditions</h3>
                <p>Welcome to RentalHub! By confirming a rental through RENTALHUB, both the Owner and the User (collectively
                    referred to as the "Parties") agree to the following Terms and Conditions, governed by the applicable laws of the 
                    Republic of the Philippines, including but not limited to: <br> <br>
                    - Republic Act No. 10173 - Data Privacy Act of 2012 <br>
                    -  Republic Act No. 7394 - Consumer Act of the Philippines <br>
                    -  Republic Act No. 8792 - E-Commerce Act of 2000 <br>
                    
                </p>

                <p><strong>1.  Governing Law</strong><br>
                    These terms are established under the laws of the Republic of the 
                    Philippines to ensure a fair, lawful, and secure rental transaction.
                </p>
                <br>
                <p><strong>2. Eligibility</strong><br>
                    Users must be at least 18 years old. <br>
                    Users must be residents of the Philippines. <br>
                    Users must be legally capable of entering into binding agreements. <br><br>
                    Legal Reference: <br>
                    Article 1327, Civil Code of the Philippines – Persons disqualified to give consent (e.g., minors) cannot enter into contracts. <br>
                    Republic Act No. 6809 – Emancipation of minors: Legal age of majority is 18 years. <br>
                    </p>
                    <br>

                <p><strong>3. Responsibility of Care</strong><br>
                    Once the item is in the User's possession, they assume full responsibility for
                     its care and security until it is returned to the Owner.<br> <br>

                    Legal Reference: <br>
                    Article 1667 - Civil Code of the Philippines, Book IV, Title VIII
                    </p>
                    <br>

                <p><strong>4. Penalties for Damages or Loss</strong><br>
                    <strong>4.1  Major Damage / Irreversible Damage</strong>
                    <p>Penalty: Three (3) times the listed price of the item. <br>
                        Examples: Broken parts, water/fire damage, permanent stains, unauthorized modifications.
                        <br><br>
                        Legal Reference: Article 1671 - Civil Code of the Philippines, Book IV, Title VIII
                        </p>
                        <strong>4.2 Minor Damage</strong>
                    <p>Penalty: 50% of the listed price for inconvenience.<br>
                        Examples: Scratches, Small Dents, Removable Stains, and Minor loose parts.
                        <br><br>
                        Legal Reference: Articles 1657 & 1671 - Civil Code of the Philippines, Book IV
                        </p>
                        <strong>4.3 Lost or Unreturned Items</strong>
                        <p>Penalty: Full replacement value is based on the current market price or purchase invoice.
                            <br><br>
                            Legal Reference: Articles 1161 & 1657 - Civil Code of the Philippines
                            </p>
                    </p>
                    <br>
                    <p><strong>5. Late Return Fee</strong><br>
                        The Owner (Lessor) and User (Lessee) shall independently agree on and handle all payment arrangements. RENTALHUB is not
                        responsible for payment processing and acts solely as a facilitator.
                        </p>
                        <br>
                        <p><strong>6. Payment Terms</strong><br>
                            If the item is not returned by the agreed date, the User 
                            shall continue to pay the full daily rental rate until the item is returned. <br>
                            Users must communicate any delays with the Owner. Failure 
                            to do so may lead to further penalties or platform suspension.
                            </p>
                            <br>
                        <p><strong>7. Termination and Legal Remedies</strong><br>
                            <strong>7.1 Termination by Owner</strong>
                            <p>Permitted in cases of late return, item misuse, or platform policy violations.</p>
                                <br>
                                <strong>7.2 Termination by User</strong>
                            <p>Permitted in cases of misrepresented items, non-delivery, or safety issues.</p>
                                <br>
                                <strong>7.3 Mutual Termination</strong>
                                <p> Allowed upon agreement or due to force majeure.
                            </p>
                            <br>
                            <p><strong>8. Limitation of Liability</strong><br>
                                RENTALHUB is not liable for any damages or disputes arising
                                from rentals. It functions only as a digital platform connecting users.
                                </p>
                                <br>
                                <p><strong>9. Communication and Delivery Disclaimer</strong><br>
                                    All communications between the Owner and the Renter, including inquiries, confirmations, and payment arrangements, are conducted outside the RENTALHUB platform. <br>
                                    RENTALHUB shall not be held liable for miscommunications or disputes resulting from these external interactions. <br>
                                    RENTALHUB is not responsible for courier handling, delivery delays, damages, or loss during shipment. <br>
                                    Delivery logistics and disputes are solely the responsibility of the Owner and Renter.
                                    </p>
                                    <br>
                                    <p><strong>10. User Conduct</strong><br>
                                        Users agree to abide by all laws, RENTALHUB policies, and not misuse the platform. <br>
                                        Activities such as fraud, misrepresentation, and harassment are strictly prohibited. <br> <br>
                                        Legal Reference: <br>
                                        Article 1306, Civil Code of the Philippines – Parties may establish terms as long as they are not contrary to law or public policy. <br>
                                        Article 19 & 20, Civil Code – Prohibits abuse of rights and actions that are contrary to morals or good customs.
                                    </p>
                                    <br>
                                    <p><strong>11. Force Majeure</strong><br>
                                        Neither party is liable for failures caused by events beyond control, such as natural disasters, government actions, or platform outages.
                                    </p>
                                    <br>
                                    <p><strong>12. Insurance Notice</strong><br>
                                         Owners are encouraged to insure high-value items. RENTALHUB does not offer or manage insurance services.
                                    </p>
                                    <br>
                                    <p><strong>13. Data Privacy</strong><br>
                                        By signing up, the User consents to the lawful collection and processing of their personal data. <br>
                                        Data collected includes identity, contact details, and other relevant account information. <br>
                                        The information will be used solely for verification, communication, and rental-related services. <br> <br>
                                        Legal Reference: <br>
                                        Republic Act No. 10173 – Data Privacy Act of 2012 <br>
                                        Section 12: Criteria for Lawful Processing of Personal Information <br>
                                        Section 16: Rights of the Data Subject
                                    </p>
                                    <br>
                                    <p><strong>14. Acceptance of Terms</strong><br>
                                        By clicking Sign Up, the User confirms that they: <br>
                                        Have read and understood the Terms and Conditions <br>
                                        Consent to the use of their data under RA 10173 <br>
                                        Are eligible to create an account <br>
                                        Will comply with all RENTALHUB platform rules and responsibilities
                                        </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <button type="submit" class="btn primary">CREATE</button>
    </form>
    <a href="/login">Already have an account?</a>
</div>

